{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "04", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "22", "M": "44", "S": "38"}}, "news": [{"title": "Prime minister to lay foundation stone for Jaipur metro phase-II on July 4", "para": "Prime Minister Narendra Modi is inaugurating Phase II of the Jaipur Metro, a five-year project set to revolutionize connectivity along Tonk Road. This expansion includes a significant elevated stretch from Sitapura to Pinjrapole and an underground section near the airport.  Traffic management plans are in place to minimize disruption, with a focus on creating a 'Model Corridor' to ensure smooth commutes during construction.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/prime-minister-modi-to-launch-jaipur-metro-phase-ii-construction-on-july-4/132174484?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-185968/132174484.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "No misappropriation of flats, TDR in Kothrud SRA scheme: Maharashtra minister", "para": "State minister Shambhuraj Desai has denied any misappropriation of flats or fraudulent transfer of development rights in Pune's Kothrud slum rehabilitation project. Responding to allegations of fake beneficiaries and financial loss, Desai stated due process was followed. The urban development department will review submitted documents and hold a meeting to address the concerns raised by MLA Sunil Kamble and other elected members regarding SRA schemes.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/maharashtra-minister-denies-misappropriation-in-kothrud-sra-housing-project/132174383?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1026461/132174383.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Aadhaar e-KYC, QR code a must for property registration in Haryana", "para": "Haryana has revolutionized property registration with a new tech-driven system. Aadhaar e-KYC, biometrics, and digital signatures are now mandatory, enhancing security and transparency. Registered documents will feature QR codes for instant verification, combating fraud. The process is streamlined, eliminating physical NOCs and allowing online tracking, document uploads, and even Tatkal upgrades for urgent needs. This initiative aims to save time and money for citizens while curbing fraudulent practices.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/haryana-mandates-aadhaar-e-kyc-and-qr-codes-for-property-registration/132174269?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-416242/132174269.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}